So when I got this job offer,
I couldn't refuse.

240
00:09:56,121 --> 00:09:57,772
I've missed so many
firsts in Rachel's life.

241
00:09:57,823 --> 00:09:59,490
I was not about to
do that with Beth.

242
00:09:59,575 --> 00:10:00,792
Neat story,

243
00:10:00,876 --> 00:10:02,877
but I'm late for
a meeting on the roof.

244
00:10:02,944 --> 00:10:04,579
Quinn, just listen to her.
Hey. Look.

245
00:10:04,630 --> 00:10:07,465
Since the day that I gave
Rachel up for adoption,

246
00:10:07,549 --> 00:10:09,250
I have been walking through life

247
00:10:09,301 --> 00:10:12,003
searching for her face
everywhere I go.

248
00:10:12,087 --> 00:10:14,889
Imagining what she's doing,
what she may be like...

249
00:10:14,956 --> 00:10:16,974
I don't want you to go
through what I went through.

250
00:10:17,059 --> 00:10:19,177
Part of me is-is
back here because...

251
00:10:19,261 --> 00:10:20,812
because I want you
to get to know Beth.

252
00:10:20,896 --> 00:10:23,064
I want you to be
a part of her life.

253
00:10:23,131 --> 00:10:26,367
When do I get to see her?

254
00:10:26,435 --> 00:10:28,803
Are you okay?
What's going on with you?

255
00:10:28,854 --> 00:10:30,188
Are you even in Glee anymore?

256
00:10:30,272 --> 00:10:31,489
Did you come here
just to torment me

257
00:10:31,573 --> 00:10:32,857
with the idea of
seeing my child?

258
00:10:32,941 --> 00:10:35,943
Look. I want you to be
a part of Beth's life.

259
00:10:35,994 --> 00:10:37,995
But not like this.

260
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:39,914
If you're really
serious about Beth,

261
00:10:39,982 --> 00:10:42,533
clean up your act.
You think you can
tell me what to do?

262
00:10:42,618 --> 00:10:44,535
Just cause you signed
a couple of papers?

263
00:10:44,620 --> 00:10:46,671
You're not her mom!
I'm her mom!

264
00:10:46,755 --> 00:10:47,988
Quinn...
Me! So...

265
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:51,325
You can pretend
all you want,

266
00:10:51,376 --> 00:10:54,558
but that is something you
are never going to be.

267
00:11:01,927 --> 00:11:01,927
+

268
00:11:10,291 --> 00:11:13,344
MERCEDES: Listen, Mr. Shue,
I'm all for participating,

269
00:11:13,428 --> 00:11:15,012
but Shay says I'm more
of a park and bark

270
00:11:15,096 --> 00:11:16,547
and I tend to agree.

271
00:11:16,631 --> 00:11:17,848
A what and what?

272
00:11:17,932 --> 00:11:19,967
Park and bark--
I stand center stage

273
00:11:20,018 --> 00:11:21,518
singing the notes
no one else can

274
00:11:21,603 --> 00:11:23,170
while all of you guys
dance around me.

275
00:11:23,221 --> 00:11:25,389
Booty Camp is about
all of you dancing, Mercedes.

276
00:11:25,473 --> 00:11:26,523
In unison.

277
00:11:26,608 --> 00:11:27,941
I mean, look at
Vocal Adrenaline.

278
00:11:28,009 --> 00:11:30,110
When they're in synch--
one big terrifying machine,

279
00:11:30,178 --> 00:11:32,196
they're unstoppable.

280
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:34,281
Mike, do your thing.
Let's go.

281
00:11:34,348 --> 00:11:36,817
The jazz square, the grapevine,
step-touch,

282
00:11:36,868 --> 00:11:39,403
the kick ball change,
and pivot.

283
00:11:39,487 --> 00:11:42,156
We perfect these basics,
we'll win Nationals.

284
00:11:42,207 --> 00:11:43,540
Grapevine to
the right.

285
00:11:43,625 --> 00:11:44,825
Five, six, seven, eight.

286
00:11:44,876 --> 00:11:46,526
Keep it going.

287
00:11:46,578 --> 00:11:48,712
I-- am-- in-- hell.

288
00:11:48,797 --> 00:11:50,497
I'm going to put
my light under a bushel,

289
00:11:50,548 --> 00:11:52,249
