for the auditions tomorrow.

290
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:54,468
BLAINE:
I'm still trying to decide

291
00:11:54,535 --> 00:11:55,919
between "Maria"
and "Something's Coming."

292
00:11:56,004 --> 00:11:58,705
Those are Tony songs. Are you
auditioning for Tony, too?

293
00:11:58,757 --> 00:12:00,891
Would that be weird?
No, no, not at all.

294
00:12:00,975 --> 00:12:02,375
You'd be a great Tony.

295
00:12:02,427 --> 00:12:04,344
Be the perfect Tony actually,
in some respects.

296
00:12:04,396 --> 00:12:07,264
MIKE: Finn, you look like
you're stepping on bees.

297
00:12:07,348 --> 00:12:08,399
Come on,
Mercedes, blend.

298
00:12:08,483 --> 00:12:11,402
Well, except I'm a junior.

299
00:12:11,486 --> 00:12:13,153
Tony's the lead.

300
00:12:13,221 --> 00:12:15,489
Which means that a senior should
probably play that part.

301
00:12:15,556 --> 00:12:17,825
Yeah, that is kind
of how it works, huh?

302
00:12:17,892 --> 00:12:19,576
I'd be fine with Bernardo
or Officer Krupke.

303
00:12:19,661 --> 00:12:21,995
as long as it was
opposite your Tony.

304
00:12:22,063 --> 00:12:23,914
Kurt, jazz hands.
Fine.

305
