365
00:16:39,954 --> 00:16:41,922
<i>SUE:
Quinn Fabray used to be
on top of the world.</i>

366
00:16:41,989 --> 00:16:43,874
<i>She had it all.</i>

367
00:16:43,958 --> 00:16:48,995
<i>But now she walks the hallways
of McKinley High broken, alone.</i>

368
00:16:49,047 --> 00:16:51,965
<i>What happened, Quinn Fabray?</i>

369
00:16:52,016 --> 00:16:54,434
I got involved in the arts.

370
00:16:54,502 --> 00:16:58,505
SUE: And now after a long
day of snorting Splenda
and cutting class,

371
00:16:58,556 --> 00:17:01,775
she kills the pain the
only way she knows how--

372
00:17:01,842 --> 00:17:04,277
smoking corn starch.

373
00:17:04,345 --> 00:17:06,646
Wait, what?

374
00:17:06,698 --> 00:17:09,483
Cut. The dummy could not
remember her lines, Coach.

375
00:17:09,534 --> 00:17:12,619
Now remember, just like
we rehearsed it.

376
00:17:12,686 --> 00:17:15,489
Mr. Schuester, I came here to
give you a piece of my mind.

377
00:17:15,540 --> 00:17:16,873
What's going on here?

378
00:17:16,958 --> 00:17:18,208
Rolling.
I used to have everything.

379
00:17:18,292 --> 00:17:20,327
Dated the quarterback
of the football team,

380
00:17:20,378 --> 00:17:22,496
was the captain of the Cheerios!

381
00:17:22,547 --> 00:17:24,464
I was the prettiest, most
popular girl at this school

382
00:17:24,532 --> 00:17:26,833
until I joined Glee Club,
and then it all went to hell.

383
00:17:26,884 --> 00:17:30,137
SUE:
This is campaign dynamite.
I just want you to know

384
00:17:30,204 --> 00:17:34,424
that I am never coming back
to Glee Club-- ever.

385
00:17:34,509 --> 00:17:36,709
Do you understand?
I hope you're happy.

386
00:17:36,761 --> 00:17:38,011
Ms. Fabray,

387
00:17:38,062 --> 00:17:39,763
wait.

388
00:17:39,847 --> 00:17:41,714
You know, there's only one
person in this world

389
00:17:41,766 --> 00:17:43,150
that you care about
and that's yourself.

390
00:17:43,217 --> 00:17:44,935
You have no idea...
I'm not finished!

391
00:17:45,019 --> 00:17:47,070
Whoa.
You're not a little girl
anymore, Quinn.

392
00:17:47,155 --> 00:17:49,740
How long do you plan
on playing the victim card?

393
00:17:49,824 --> 00:17:52,192
Since day one, you've done
nothing but sabotage

394
00:17:52,243 --> 00:17:55,612
the same Glee Club that
has been there for you
over and over again.

395
00:17:55,696 --> 00:17:57,998
When you got pregnant,
when your parents
kicked you out,

396
00:17:58,065 --> 00:17:59,783
Mercedes even let
you live at her house.

397
00:17:59,867 --> 00:18:02,285
And I don't recall ever hearing
so much as a thank you.

398
00:18:02,370 --> 00:18:05,422
So now you're a train wreck.
Well, congratulations.

399
00:18:05,506 --> 00:18:08,908
But you stride into my office
and tell me that it's my fault?

400
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:11,178
Well, then,

401
00:18:11,245 --> 00:18:13,096
I have something
to say to you.

402
00:18:13,181 --> 00:18:14,681
Grow up.

403
00:18:17,268 --> 00:18:19,419
Would you turn that thing off?

404
00:18:19,470 --> 00:18:21,438
And... cut.

405
00:18:21,522 --> 00:18:23,273
Fantastic. I got...

406
00:18:23,357 --> 00:18:25,225
Oh, no, damn it.

407
00:18:25,276 --> 00:18:27,694
My finger was over the thingie.
I didn't get any of that.

408
00:18:27,761 --> 00:18:28,595
Come on, Becky.

409
00:18:28,646 --> 00:18:29,813
That was really sexy.

410
00:18:32,950 --> 00:18:34,284
(doorbell ringing)

411
00:18:44,662 --> 00:18:46,913
(doorbell ringing)

412
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:54,721
Hey.

413
00:18:54,788 --> 00:18:57,474
I hope it's okay that
I just stopped by.

414
00:18:57,558 --> 00:19:00,093
How do you know
where I live?

415
00:19:00,144 --> 00:19:04,797
Um, I have friends
in law enforcement.

416
00:19:04,849 --> 00:19:07,967
Noah, I told you, I want you
to be a part of Beth's life,

417
00:19:08,019 --> 00:19:10,821
but on my terms. You can't
just barge in on me like this.

418
00:19:10,905 --> 00:19:12,155
Here's a drug test.

419
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:14,241
See? Totally clean.

420
00:19:14,308 --> 00:19:17,110
I also haven't had
a drink since we
talked-- besides beer.

421
00:19:17,161 --> 00:19:19,913
I even did some homework.
Turns out Napoleon,

422
00:19:19,980 --> 00:19:22,315
not just a dessert--
he was a real dude.

423
00:19:22,366 --> 00:19:23,667
Well, that is great.

424
00:19:23,751 --> 00:19:26,986
I'm-- honestly I'm
truly impressed.

425
00:19:27,038 --> 00:19:30,207
But having a relationship
with a child isn't about
little bursts of energy.

426
00:19:30,291 --> 00:19:32,175
This is a long-term commitment.

427
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:33,260
(Beth crying)

428
00:19:33,327 --> 00:19:34,845
Crap, she's awake.

429
00:19:34,929 --> 00:19:36,213
Hi, sweetie.

430
00:19:36,297 --> 00:19:38,348
Come here.

431
00:19:38,432 --> 00:19:41,718
Oh, that's it.
(sighs)

432
00:19:41,802 --> 00:19:45,305
Okay. It's okay.

433
00:19:45,356 --> 00:19:46,907
It's okay.

434
00:19:50,311 --> 00:19:52,062
My God, she
looks like Quinn.

435
00:19:52,146 --> 00:19:53,864
And you.

436
00:19:53,948 --> 00:19:55,699
She has that same
dopey smile.

437
00:19:55,783 --> 00:19:57,734
Can you say hi?

438
00:19:57,818 --> 00:19:59,486
(laughing)

439
00:19:59,537 --> 00:20:01,821
I was happy, you know,

440
00:20:01,873 --> 00:20:04,991
that she was with you,
and it made it easier.

441
00:20:05,042 --> 00:20:06,576
I drew her a picture.

442
00:20:08,996 --> 00:20:10,714
It was supposed to be a clown,

443
00:20:10,798 --> 00:20:12,666
but it kind of turned out
like a pig,

444
00:20:12,717 --> 00:20:14,668
so I call it
a clown pig.

445
00:20:14,719 --> 00:20:16,336
It's kind of my own
made-up animal.

446
00:20:16,387 --> 00:20:18,037
Look what he drew us.
Huh?

447
00:20:18,089 --> 00:20:20,206
Thought it might
make her think of me.

448
00:20:20,258 --> 00:20:21,675
(chuckles)

449
00:20:21,726 --> 00:20:23,543
You don't think it will
scare her, do you?

450
00:20:23,594 --> 00:20:25,395
No. She'll be okay.

451
00:20:25,479 --> 00:20:27,147
She's tough.

452
00:20:28,933 --> 00:20:30,684
Do you want to hold her?

453
00:20:34,438 --> 00:20:36,022
Can he hold you?

454
00:20:36,073 --> 00:20:38,224
If he takes your blankie,
can he hold you?

455
00:20:38,276 --> 00:20:39,993
I don't want
to freak her out.

456
00:20:40,060 --> 00:20:42,395
We'll work up to it.

457
00:20:42,446 --> 00:20:44,397
I'll do anything--

458
00:20:44,448 --> 00:20:48,668
anything to prove to you
that I can be in her life.

459
00:20:48,736 --> 00:20:51,004
Please just give
me that chance.

460
00:20:56,740 --> 00:20:56,740
+

461
00:20:59,669 --> 00:21:00,752
Here you go, buddy.

462
00:21:00,803 --> 00:21:02,387
Thanks, Coach.

463
00:21:02,455 --> 00:21:04,172
She's like my own
private Jim Henson.

464
00:21:04,257 --> 00:21:05,340
Next.

465
00:21:07,427 --> 00:21:08,793
Hello. I'm Kurt Hummel.

466
00:21:08,845 --> 00:21:10,846
And I'll be auditioning
for the role of Tony.

467
00:21:10,930 --> 00:21:11,980
The male lead.

468
00:21:12,065 --> 00:21:13,315
That's great, Kurt.

469
00:21:13,399 --> 00:21:15,851
I'll be performing the seminal,
and in my case,

470
00:21:15,935 --> 00:21:17,402
